<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 2:32PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Armstrong and eastern Randall Counties through 330 PM CDT...
At 232 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Palo Duro Canyon, or 14 miles east of Canyon, moving northwest at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Canyon, Lake Tanglewood, Palo Duro Canyon and Timbercreek Canyon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
